snippet.textDisplay: We al knew that Hopper was coming back, but there was still a part of me deep down that was hoping he would actually be dead. I know this is an unpopular opinion, but I just feel that if they did kill him off that would show they aren’t afraid of killing a main character which is really good. Unfortunately he’s still alive and we haven’t seen any main character die yet besides Billy who was a side character until the 3rd season. The reason I don’t really count Billy as a main character death is because we never really got to know him enough to mourn his death. He didn’t have any character change from being a prick until the very end when he sacrifices himself for eleven. Bob doesn’t really count either because he dies the same season that he’s introduced. He has the same problem as Billy where we don’t get to know him enough to really mourn his death. I’m pretty sure the majority of the people were more upset because he was in Lord of The Rings. All we really know about him is that he’s a tech guy who likes Joyce. Hopper on the other hand has been a main character since season 1. He was one of the fan favorites and we’ve seen lots of growth wether that be good or bad form him. He started as somewhat of a wreck after the loss of his daughter to a man who wanted to protect his new daughter who was eleven. She starts to defy him after she grows up like most kids do and this makes him angry and even more protective because he doesn’t want to lose her. He is in this constant downward spiral during the third season from threatening mike to just shooting people without a second thought. He’s had many ups and downs and seeing his end in the third season would’ve been really good. Hell I cried when he “died.” But now all of that has been undone because plot twist but not really, he’s still alive.

I bet the story will be something like this: the Russians are trying to open the portal to the other world only to accidently let out the mindflayer's drunken uncle "Vladoflayer" who tries to take controll over Russia by causing the Chernobly disaster and using the radiation there to gain strength and create his army of vodlings. However he is also a alcoholic and drinks beyond russian standards making him incapable to carry out his masterplan without delays. David Harbour finds out about this and has to battle Vladoflayer alone but then they have a conversation in english.
Vladoflayer: "I will rule this worlds alcohol industry and every 30 days you must have drunk a whole bottle of vodka in one shot or else it's your life."
David Harbour: "I can survive anything."
Then after a few episodes the gang from America come to Russia and defeat Vladoflayer as the girl gains her super powers back and cures his alcoholism only to make him addicted to something else, crack. Season 5 will take place in Colombia with Vladoflayer and Pablo Escobar teaming up and taking over the drug industry. After the heros defeat Escobar Vladoflayer escapes to the secret facility in space and brings back Mindflayer in Season 6 as the heros have to stop them both before they use the super lazer to piss on the moon but fail and now one of the uninteresting main characters is dead. In season 7 both flayers are beaten and sent to the sun. In season 8... eh... we don't know anymore just come watch it anyway.
